<div id="banner">
	<h1>Zooko and Seth in RSS</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Since I&#8217;m spending more and more time in NetNewsWire, I decided to RSSify the few remaining sites I read. First off I did <a href="http://zooko.com/log">Zooko&#8217;s website</a>: <a href="../2002/zooko">RSS feed</a>. If you don&#8217;t read Zooko&#8217;s blog, the <a href="../2002/zooko.py">source code</a>, while very messy, might still be useful for scraping a site you like.</p>

<p>I modified it to create <a href="../2002/vitanuova">another scraper</a> (<a href="../2002/vitanuova.py">source</a>) for <a href="http://vitanuova.loyalty.org/">Vitanuova</a>, which has become my absolute favorite living web site. It doesn&#8217;t do much, but it does let my aggregator notify me when there&#8217;s an update, which is nice.</p>

<p class="posted">posted August 27, 2002 11:27 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000532" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

